SYNOPSIS
        #include <debug_message.h>

	void debug_message(string text)
	void debug_message(string text, int target)

DESCRIPTION
	Prints the given text to stdout, stderr, the <host>.debug.log file,
        or any combination of these.
        
        <target> is a combination of the bitflags DMSG_STDOUT, DMSG_STDERR,
        and DMSG_LOGFILE and determines the target of the log output. If
        given as 0 or not given at all, the efun will log to stdout and
        into the <host>.debug.log file.

EXAMPLE
        debug_message("This goes to stdout and the logfile.\n");
        debug_message("This goes to stderr.\n", DMSG_STDERR);
        debug_message("This goes to stdout and stderr.\n"
                     , DMSG_STDOUT | DMSG_STDERR);

HISTORY
	Introduced in 3.2.1@34
        LDMud 3.2.9 introduced the <target> parameter.

SEE ALSO
	last_instructions(E)
